yingyinNormal.en: But just imagine, a soldier the size of an insect. The ultimate secret weapon.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不过设想一下，一个昆虫般大小的战士，一件终极秘密武器。

yingyinNormal.en: Having been delivered by an insect, two cells from the pollen burrow deep into the flower's ovary.
yingyinNormal.zh: 昆虫将花粉运送到花柱上，每粒花粉中都有两个细胞它们一路向下，进入花朵的子房。

yingyinNormal.en: Dr. Cooper has taken a relatively boring subject and managed to make it completely insufferable. Plus, he looks like a giant insect.
yingyinNormal.zh: "库珀博士选择的话题相当无聊，并且他成功地升级到了令人无法忍受的地步，另外，他看起来像只大昆虫"。

yingyinNormal.en: Of course I can. I can identify every insect and arachnid on the planet. Not that that's going to keep me from having to move in with my daughter in Oxnard. And we're not talking Oxnard at the beach. No! We're talking Oxnard in the onion fields.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我当然能。我能认出全世界所有的昆虫和节肢动物，但我也一样得去投奔我住在奥克斯纳德的女儿，而且这不是海滩旁边的奥克斯纳德，我们说的是葱地中间的奥克斯纳德。

yingyinNormal.en: Be gone insect operative, your work is done. Your Excellency.
yingyinNormal.zh: 蝼蚁工人滚吧，没你的事儿了。是，阁下。

yingyinNormal.en: Pedro is talking to his sticky insect. A sticky insect is an insect that looks like a stick.
yingyinNormal.zh: 佩德罗正在和竹节虫说话。竹节虫是一种虫子，就像一根棍子一样。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm going to bring my pet gold fish. I'm going to bring my sticky insect. I'll bring my gecko.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那我可以把我的金鱼金金带来学校。我要把我的竹节虫带过来。我要把我的壁虎带过来。

yingyinNormal.en: Wonderful. And who is this? This is my sticky insect. What's his name? Steven. What does he do? He looks like a stick.
yingyinNormal.zh: 真是太棒了！那么这个是谁的呢？这个就是我的竹节虫了。他叫什么名字？史蒂夫。那他会做什么呢？他看起来像一个棍子。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: Healthy trees are also better able to fend off <highlight>insects</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 健康的树种防御虫害的能力更加强大。

examination_example.sentence: Subsequent experiments reproduced this effect with other stimuli, such as the sound of fingernails on a chalkboard and photographs of disgusting <highlight>insects</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 随后的实验在其他刺激物上重现了这种效果，比如指甲在黑板上的声音和恶心昆虫的照片。

examination_example.sentence: Ants keep predatory <highlight>insects</highlight> away from where their aphids feed; Gmail keeps the spammers out of our inboxes.

数据源自2016.6-2023.6年8年间全六级试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight>考纲释义</highlight>
精选实考、考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2016-2023年51套试卷，包括阅读、听力、翻译等所有题型。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2016-2023年8年间全六级试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: The <highlight>insect</highlight>, Tutaabsoluta, has destroyed 80% of farms in Kaduna, Nigeria's largest tomato producing state, leading the government there to declare a state of emergency.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这种名为 Tutaabsoluta 的昆虫摧毁了尼日利亚(Nigeria)最大的番茄产地卡杜纳(Kaduna)80%的农场，当地政府宣布进入紧急状态。

examination_example.sentence: In Nigeria, where tomatoes are a staple of local diets, the <highlight>insect</highlight>'s effects are devastating.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 因为在尼日利亚，西红柿是当地的主食，这种昆虫的影响是毁灭性的。

examination_example.sentence: Now, Africa's largest economy is facing a food crisis as major tomato fields have been destroyed by an <highlight>insect</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 现在，这个非洲最大的经济体正面临一场粮食危机，大量的番茄田被某昆虫摧毁。

examination_example.sentence: The <highlight>insect</highlight>, also known as the tomato leaf miner, devastates crops by feeding on fruits and digging into and moving through stalks.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这种昆虫也被称为番茄叶矿虫，它以水果为食，钻进植物茎杆活动，进而破坏农作物。

examination_example.sentence: White storks feed on locusts (蝗虫) and other <highlight>insects</highlight> that can become pests if their numbers get out of hand.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 白鹳以蝗虫和其他昆虫为食，如果这些昆虫的数量失控，它们就会变成害虫。

examination_example.sentence: Mary shut the window just now so that she could keep the <highlight>insects</highlight> out.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 玛丽刚才关上了窗，这样昆虫就进不来了。

examination_example.sentence: In the winter there aren't any <highlight>insects</highlight>, so the birds fly south to southern Europe and Africa.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 冬季，这里没有昆虫，所以鸟群朝南飞向欧洲南部和非洲。

examination_example.sentence: But most people probably won’t want to see the <highlight>insects</highlight> they eat.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但大多数人也许并不想看到自己吃的昆虫是什么样子。
